<h2 id="Mounts">Mounts</h2>
<p>
    Mounts in Guild Wars 2 all have unique skills and try to fill a niche role. Once you unlock a mount, it unlocks account wide.
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <h3 class="raptor">
            <image src="https://render.guildwars2.com/file/2F4AAA52F573C5425BFCD7525FB70C9E6DCAD791/1766903.png" alt="raptor" style="width:50px;" />
            <a href="https://wiki.guildwars2.com/wiki/Raptor" target="_blank">Raptor</a>
        </h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Unlock: Owning ANY expansion OR the Guild Wars 2 Starter Pack and being level 10 or above.
            </li>
            <li>
                Masteries: <span class="pof">Path of Fire</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                Combat Mount: NO
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    As your first mount, the <span class="raptor">Raptor</span> is a good A to B mount, having an average run speed, and a jump that lets you traverse any smaller gaps with ease.
                    Once you train the masteries, your <span class="raptor">Raptor</span> will jump further and pull enemies together with Tail Spin.
                    At max mastery, it increases the damage of all the other mounts engage skills.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <h3 class="springer">
            <image src="https://render.guildwars2.com/file/EAD3540691D702A52E617140055725DF41BBBA49/1766899.png" alt="Springer" style="width:50px;" />
            <a href="https://wiki.guildwars2.com/wiki/Springer" target="_blank">Springer</a>
        </h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Unlock: <span class="pof">Path of Fire</span> || <span class="eod">End of Dragons</span> || <span class="jw">Janthir Wilds</span> || <span class="voe">Visions of Eternity</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                Masteries: <span class="pof">Path of Fire</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                Combat Mount: NO
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    The <span class="springer">Springer</span> is the second mount you can get in PoF, after <span class="raptor">Raptor</span>.
                    It can jump high and has a high CC dismount skill.
                    Training the masteries will let the <span class="springer">Springer</span> jump higher, have more CC on Cannonball, and reduces it's fall damage.
                    At max mastery, all mounts gain the reduced fall damage.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Sadly, the <span class="springer">Springer</span> gets outclassed in both how high it can jump, and how much CC it can do.
                    The <span class="skyscale">Skyscale</span> can scale significantly higher cliffs,
                    and the <span class="warclaw">Warclaw</span> can do significantly more breakbar damage.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>        
    </li>
    <!--CCMovementMount1-->
